---
description: MoonDB REST API patterns and query syntax
alwaysApply: false
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,py,rb,go,rs}"
---

moondb-api-patterns:

- Base URL pattern: https://api.moondb.ai/p/{project_id}
- CRUD endpoints: GET/POST /api/{table}, GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/{table}/{id}, POST /api/{table}/bulk
- Filter syntax: ?field=op.value (operators: eq, neq, gt, gte, lt, lte, like, in, is_null, not_null)
- Sort: ?sort=field.desc or ?sort=field.asc
- Pagination: ?limit=20&offset=0
- Field selection: ?select=id,name,email
- Include related records: ?include=user_id (expands ref columns into full objects)
- List response: { data: [...], meta: { total, limit, offset, has_more } }
- Single response: { data: { ...row } }
- Error response: { error: { code, message, suggestion } } — always read `suggestion` to self-correct
- Auth endpoints (when auth_table exists):
  - POST /auth/signup { email, password } → { data: { token, refresh_token, user } }
  - POST /auth/login { email, password } → { data: { token, refresh_token, user } }
  - POST /auth/refresh { refresh_token } → { data: { token, refresh_token } }
  - GET /auth/me (Bearer token) → { data: { user } }
  - PATCH /auth/me { display_name, ... } → { data: { user } }
  - POST /auth/logout (Bearer token)
  - POST /auth/change-password { current_password, new_password } (Bearer token)
  - POST /auth/forgot-password { email, redirect_url } → sends reset email (always 200)
  - POST /auth/reset-password { token, new_password } → resets password
- Token expires in 1 hour. Use refresh_token (30 days) for renewal.
- Headers: Authorization: Bearer {token} for auth, X-Public-Key: pk_... for public reads, X-Admin-Key: sk_... for admin ops
- File upload: POST /storage/upload (multipart/form-data with file, table, column, row_id). After upload, store url in the file column via PATCH.
- AI endpoints: POST /ai/{endpoint_name} { "param": "value" }. Text models: gemma (fast), gpt-oss (intelligent). Image models: flux-schnell (fast), flux-dev (photorealistic).
